Want to re-imagine how the world's largest omni-channel consumer database can be used to power targeted ad campaigns for the largest brands in the world? We are rethinking digital advertising here at Walmart and are looking for some great people to help make this happen.&nbsp;&nbsp;At Walmart Connect, We connect brands more meaningfully in customers’ everyday lives to accelerate shared growth. As stewards of our brand promise, “Save Money. Live Better,” we work alongside some of the most talented people in the world to engage with the more than 150M households who shop with us each week. This is a unique opportunity to join a high-visibility team with a big impact on our omni-channel business. We believe all digital advertising across search and display, both in-store and online, can be targeted, effective and accountable -- and we have Walmart's retail sales data to prove it&nbsp;&nbsp;Position Summary... What You'll Do...&nbsp;&nbsp;We are looking for a Strategy & Business Development Senior Manager to join Walmart Connect’s (WMC) in-house Strategy team and help define new business opportunities. The WMC Strategy team is envisioning the future of WMC and its important role within Walmart.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In this role, you will help us formulate the future of retail advertising by defining and evaluating new strategies and businesses to grow Walmart Connect including partnerships, omnichannel partnerships, pilot program management, and M&A to achieve that growth goal. We will need your strategic and critical-thinking skills to build upon our strengths and complement our offerings. You will scope market potential, evaluate competitors and identify what it takes to build a winning business while creating a set of actionable recommendations for WMC leadership and Walmart executives.&nbsp;&nbsp;Come join the team if you are:&nbsp; Excited about the future of retail & media&nbsp;&nbsp; Constantly thinking about the customer experience first&nbsp; Passionate about technology, retail, or advertising including trends and competition&nbsp; A critical thinker with the ability to distill complicated concepts into actionable strategies&nbsp; Analytical with deep financial modeling experience to drive decision making&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand how to evaluate and recommend buy/partner/build&nbsp; Able to influence and inspire action cross-functionally and confident about presenting recommendations to senior leadership&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsibilities&nbsp; Evaluate new strategies and opportunities for WMC including strategy definition, market opportunity sizing, competitive evaluation, business case building and identification of execution enablers that reinforce WMC strategies through differentiation/competitive advantage&nbsp; Build detailed, driver-level financial models and business scenario cases to inform planning and decision making&nbsp; Identify possible M&A or strategic partnerships to accelerate strategies including analyzing competitors, identifying capabilities acceleration, and leading business perspective in cross functional build/buy/partner analyses&nbsp; Drive cross functional consensus building and developing partnership across stakeholders in strategy evaluation&nbsp; Communicate WMC’s strategy, new business ideas and opportunities to leadership ranging from WMC business leaders to Walmart executives&nbsp; Evaluate strategic partnerships to accelerate new offering’s go-to-market timeline&nbsp; Collaborate across Walmart enterprise business partners and build strong cross enterprise relationships&nbsp;&nbsp; Qualifications&nbsp; 3 to 5+ years of relevant experience in retail/e-commerce, advertising, technology, or consulting/investment banking and an “always on” attitude towards gaining more knowledge and leadership in these areas&nbsp; Demonstrated knowledge of the digital advertising, technology and retail landscape and interest or experience with emerging technologies and retail or advertising trends&nbsp; Comfort with ambiguity and experience with scoping new ideas or innovation&nbsp; Strong quantitative skills and demonstrated ability to develop complex, driver level financial models&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong presentation, communication and influencing skills and comfort in interacting with executive level business and technical partners&nbsp; Intellectually curious, high energy, and strong work ethic and ability to manage multiple high-visibility projects at one time&nbsp; MBA required&nbsp; &nbsp;Primary Locations&nbsp;221 River Street, Hoboken, NJ 07030, United States of America; 850 Cherry Avenue, San Bruno, CA 94066, United States of America&nbsp;&nbsp;About Walmart Connect&nbsp;Want to change the face of digital advertising? Want to re-imagine how the world's largest omni-channel consumer database can be used to power targeted campaigns for the largest brands in the world? We are rethinking digital advertising here at Walmart and are looking for some great people to help make this happen.&nbsp;&nbsp;At Walmart, we enable the connection between brands and shoppers at unprecedented scale. As stewards of our brand promise, “Save Money. Live Better,” we work alongside some of the most talented people in the world to engage with the more than 150M households who shop with us each week. This is a unique opportunity to join a high-visibility team with a big impact on our omni-channel business. We believe all digital advertising across search, display, video and experiential can be targeted, effective and accountable -- and we have Walmart's retail sales data to prove it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Live our ValuesCulture Champion• Models the Walmart values to foster our culture; holds oneself and others accountable; and supports Walmart’s commitment to communities, social justice, corporate social responsibility, and sustainability; maintains and promotes the highest standards of integrity, ethics and compliance.Servant Leadership• Acts as an altruistic servant leader and is consistently humble, self-aware, honest, and transparent.Embrace ChangeCuriosity & Courage• Demonstrates curiosity and a growth mindset; fosters an environment that supports learning, innovation, and intelligent risk-taking; and exhibits resilience in the face of setbacks.Digital Transformation & Change• Seeks and implements continuous improvements and encourages the team to leverage new digital tools and ways of working.Deliver for the CustomerCustomer Focus• Delivers expected business results while putting the customer first and consistently applying an omni-merchant mindset and the EDLP and EDLC business models to all plans.Strategic Thinking• Adopts a holistic perspective that considers data, analytics, customer insights, and different parts of the business when making plans and shaping the team’s strategy.Focus on our AssociatesDiversity, Equity & Inclusion• Identifies, attracts, and retains diverse and inclusive team members; builds a high-performing team; embraces diversity in all its forms; and actively supports diversity goal programs.Collaboration & Influence• Builds strong and trusting relationships with team members and business partners; works collaboratively and cross-functionally to achieve objectives; and communicates with energy and positivity to motivate, influence, and inspire commitment and action.Talent Management• Creates a discipline and focus around developing talent, promotes an environment allowing everyone to bring their best selves to work, empowers associates and partners to act in the best interest of the customer and company, and regularly recognizes…", 'title': '2024 Summer MBA Intern: Walmart Connect Strategy', 'title_link': 'https://careers.walmart.com/us/jobs/WD1680147-2024-summer-mba-intern-walmart-connect-strategy', 'service_name': 'careers.walmart.com'}]

blocks: [{'type': 'rich_text', 'block_id': 'Ut+Yr', 'elements': [{'type': 'rich_text_section', 'elements': [{'type': 'link', 'url': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/Pattern_Careers/job/Lehi-UT/Internship---Product-Marketing_R-100508?source=Linkedin'}]}]}]
attachments: [{'image_url': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/Pattern_Careers/assets/logo', 'image_width': 1407, 'image_height': 284, 'image_bytes': 14750, 'from_url': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/Pattern_Careers/job/Lehi-UT/Internship---Product-Marketing_R-100508?source=Linkedin', 'service_icon': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/favicon.ico', 'id': 1, 'original_url': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/Pattern_Careers/job/Lehi-UT/Internship---Product-Marketing_R-100508?source=Linkedin', 'fallback': 'Internship - Product Marketing', 'text': "Job Description: Are you obsessed with data, partner success, taking action, and changing the game? If you have a whole lot of hustle and a touch of nerd, come intern with Pattern to learn, grow, and use your skills to push one of the fastest-growing companies in the US to the top of the list! Pattern is the premier partner for global ecommerce acceleration and is headquartered in the United States, Utah's Silicon Slopes tech hub—with offices in Asia, Australia, Europe, the Middle East, and North America. Valued at $2 billion, Pattern has been named one of the fastest growing tech companies in North America by Deloitte and one of best-led companies in America by Inc. More than 150 global brands like Nestle, Sylvania, Kong, Panasonic, Sorel, and Pandora rely—rely on Pattern's global ecommerce acceleration platform to scale their business around the world. We place employee experience at the center of our business model and have been recognized as one of America's Most Loved Workplaces®. We are looking for a Product Marketing Intern on the marketing team to help us continuously improve our multimedia, omni-channel content creation, distribution, and optimization. This role will collaborate cross-functionally to facilitate world-class B2B marketing projects, such as videos, podcasts, social campaigns, etc…, and contribute to key content strategies. This is a part time role that works a hybrid schedule based in Lehi, Utah. Frequently Asked Questions What is a day in the life of a Product Marketing Intern? The Product Marketing Intern will support the Product Marketing team by performing analyses of go-to-market performance and business opportunities in the market This person also conducts research on competitor behavior and build buyer insights to understand buyer personas Compile analysis and financial models on customer trends and historical data to support decision-making Lead the development and execution of ad-hoc analysis to support data-driven pricing initiatives Conduct periodic analysis on the performance of existing products (e.g. pricing, adoption trend, usage, etc.) Quantify and estimate market sizes, identify key players and market trends Design new creative analytics and visualizations to help senior management get deeper insights into performance of key areas Perform in-depth analysis of go-to-market performance (win / loss analysis, etc) to identify areas for improvement Support the development and curation of marketing collateral by conducting research What will I need to thrive in this role? Must be a junior or senior in college enrolled in a degree in Marketing, Business, or related field Superior interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills. Teachable and fast learner Self-motivated and proactive High ethical standards Experience in ecommerce or digital-first brands or marketplace commercial efforts (D2C, Amazon, <http://Walmart.com|Walmart.com>, etc.) is a plus What does high performance look like? You follow through with all assignments in a timely manner You give 100% to all tasks and projects you are given You will take full ownership of your projects and follow through to completion What is my potential for career growth? This role will introduce you to marketing, specifically B2B tech, and help you develop skills in content strategy and multimedia, integrated execution. Upon successful completion of this internship, you may be offered a full time position. What is the team like? You will work with, and be mentored by, the Sr Product Marketing Manager. You will meet with them on a regular basis to discuss your performance. This team is data driven and results oriented. You will collaborate regularly with members of your team to implement actionable solutions. Ideas and input are encouraged from all members. Sounds great! What’s the company culture? We are looking for individuals who are: Game Changers- A game changer is someone who looks at problems with an open mind and shares new ideas with team members, regularly reassesses existing plans and attaches a realistic timeline to goals, makes profitable, productive, and innovative contributions, and actively pursues improvements to Pattern’s processes and outcomes. Data Fanatics- A data fanatic is someone who recognizes problems and seeks to understand them through data, draws unbiased conclusions based on data that lead to actionable solutions, and continues to track the effects of the solutions using data. Partner Obsessed- An individual who is partner obsessed clearly explains the status of projects to partners and relies on constructive feedback, actively listens to partner’s expectations, and delivers results that exceed them, prioritizes the needs of your partners, and takes the time to create a personable experience for those interacting with Pattern. Team of Doers- Someone who is a part of a team of doers uplifts team members and recognizes their specific contributions, takes initiative to help in any circumstance, actively contributes to supporting improvements, and holds themselves accountable to the team as well as to partners. What is the hiring process? Initial phone interview with Pattern’s Talent Acquisition team Onsite interview with a panel of department leaders Executive review Offer How can I stand out as an applicant? Be prepared to talk about professional accomplishments with specific data to quantify examples Be ready to talk about how you can add value and be the best addition to the team Focus on mentioning how you would be partner obsessed at Pattern Be prepared to talk about any side projects related to data and analytics Why should I intern at Pattern? Pattern offers big opportunities to make a difference in the ecommerce industry! We are a company full of talented people that evolves quickly and often. We set big goals, work tirelessly to achieve them, and we love our Pattern community. We also believe in having fun and balancing our lives, so we offer awesome benefits that include Onsite Fitness Center Casual Dress Code Competitive Pay Pattern provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability, status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local laws. Pattern is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Ecommerce is booming. The challenges we solve are exciting. And we’re just getting started. We’re looking for talented people with plenty of hustle to change the game at Pattern. Is that you? Let's chat", 'title': 'Internship - Product Marketing', 'title_link': 'https://pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/Pattern_Careers/job/Lehi-UT/Internship---Product-Marketing_R-100508?source=Linkedin', 'service_name': 'pattern.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com'}]

attachments: [{'from_url': 'https://workday.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/Workday/job/USA-CO-Boulder/Product-Strategy-Intern_JR-81961-1', 'image_url': 'https://workday.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/Workday/assets/logo', 'image_width': 1200, 'image_height': 630, 'image_bytes': 76513, 'service_icon': 'https://workday.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/favicon.ico', 'id': 1, 'original_url': 'https://workday.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/Workday/job/USA-CO-Boulder/Product-Strategy-Intern_JR-81961-1', 'fallback': 'MBA Product Strategy Intern', 'text': 'Your work days are brighter here. At Workday, it all began with a conversation over breakfast. When our founders met at a sunny California diner, they came up with an idea to revolutionize the enterprise software market. And when we began to rise, one thing that really set us apart was our culture. A culture which was driven by our value of putting our people first. And ever since, the happiness, development, and contribution of every Workmate is central to who we are. Our Workmates believe a healthy employee-centric, collaborative culture is the essential mix of ingredients for success in business. That’s why we look after our people, communities and the planet while still being profitable. Feel encouraged to shine, however that manifests: you don’t need to hide who you are. You can feel the energy and the passion, it\'s what makes us unique. Inspired to make a brighter work day for all and transform with us to the next stage of our growth journey? Bring your brightest version of you and have a brighter work day here. About the Team The Office of the CHRO Product Strategy team oversees the product strategy, roadmap and lifecycle of the company’s product portfolio for HCM Products. Our team defines and drives the business plan, short- and long-term growth strategy and positioning of Workday\'s products in the market. We direct the end-to-end leadership of new and existing products from inception through all phases of the product life cycle. About the Role As an MBA Intern, you will have the opportunity to work hand in hand with Product Specialists to articulate the vision and strategy for key product areas, as well as help build the sequence of steps and actions that will be required to achieve that vision. You will build the story around strategic recommendations and help to assemble presentations for our senior and executive leaders. You will also build and analyze financial models for data-driven strategy recommendations while working with Business Finance and other teams. About You Basic Qualifications: Currently pursuing an MBA degree, with a grad date of no earlier than Dec 2024 Pursuing a major in Business, Marketing, Finance, or an equivalent field Able to commit to a full-time internship program for 12 weeks during the summer of 2024. You will return to university studies after the conclusion of the internship. Other Qualifications: Experience or coursework related to Human Resources, Product Development or Product Strategy, financial analyst, data analyst, market research You are a critical thinker with an analytical approach. A highly motivated, quick learner, who thrives on creatively and solving tough problems. Good verbal and written communication skills with the ability to easily and intuitively adapt content to various types of audiences. Propensity to be curious and explore new ideas and information Listens actively to understand others’ points of view Workday Internship Program Ready for your career to shine? At Workday, we believe that the next generation of talent is essential to our success, which is why we seek hard-working students with open minds, new perspectives, and bright ideas to join our Intern & Co-Op Program. During either the 12-week internship or multi-month co-op experience, you’ll make an impact at Workday by engaging in meaningful work, all the while forging professional connections, and strengthening your skills in an encouraging environment. Plus, you’ll be encouraged to bring your brightest self to work with coaching and mentorship, connection events and exposure to Workday’s stellar culture while living our Core Values. Let’s make workdays brighter. Apply today to start your career as a member of the Workday Intern & Co-Op Program! Workday is proud of its diverse workforce but does not sponsor employment visas or consider individuals on time-limited visas that will require sponsorship now or in the future for these positions. Workday Pay Transparency Statement - United States The annualized base salary ranges for the primary location and any additional locations in the United States (US) are listed below. Workday pay ranges vary based on work location. As a part of the total compensation package, this role may be eligible for the Workday Bonus Plan or a role-specific commission/bonus, as well as annual refresh stock grants. Recruiters can share more detail during the hiring process. Each candidate’s compensation offer will be based on multiple factors including, but not limited to, geography, experience, skills, job duties, and business need, among other things. For more information regarding Workday’s comprehensive benefits, please click here. Primary Location: USA.CO.Boulder Primary Location Base Pay Range: $49,900 - $115,000 Additional US Location(s) Base Pay Range: $47,400 - $115,000 Our Approach to Flexible Work With Flex Work, we’re combining the best of both worlds: in-person time and remote. Our approach enables our teams to deepen connections, maintain a strong community, and do their best work. We know that flexibility can take shape in many ways, so rather than a number of required days in-office each week, we simply spend at least half (50%) of our time each quarter in the office or in the field with our customers, prospects, and partners (depending on role). This means you\'ll have the freedom to create a flexible schedule that caters to your business, team, and personal needs, while being intentional to make the most of time spent together. Those in our remote "home office" roles also have the opportunity to come together in our offices for important moments that matter. Pursuant to applicable Fair Chance law, Workday will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records. Workday is an Equal Opportunity Employer including individuals with disabilities and protected veterans. Are you being referred to one of our roles? If so, ask your connection at Workday about our Employee Referral process! Join our talent community and receive the latest Workday news, content, and be first in line for new job opportunities. Those in our remote "home office" roles also have the opportunity to come together in our offices for important moments that matter. At Workday, our employees have always been our number one Core Value. We understand that everyone has unique experiences and perspectives which is why our mission is to create a safe space where all people and ideas are welcomed. Our commitment to value inclusion, belonging, and equity (VIBE™) and creating a brighter workday for all is the cornerstone of all we do. Join us! Workday is a leading provider of enterprise cloud applications for finance and human resources. Founded in 2005, Workday delivers financial management, human capital management, and analytics applications designed for the world\'s largest companies, educational institutions, and government agencies. Organizations ranging from medium-sized businesses to Fortune 50 enterprises have selected Workday. Workday is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. text:
<!channel> - need responses on another travel question for Scott & Barry.

They're looking at a potential flight leaving SLC on Dec 31st. Indicate which of the following applies to your situation:
> :+1::skin-tone-3: - I can fly that afternoon and am okay with the idea - more time in PH!
> :shrug::skin-tone-3: - I can technically make it, but not the biggest fan.
> :no_good::skin-tone-3: - I logistically cannot make that work.
As context, we're having a bit of difficulty in getting the BYU Travel office to book some of the better-priced flights. We've opened up negotiations (Gretel and I are going to bat on this, guys - probably using up some social capital in the process :joy:). But in the meantime, Barry and Scott want to do a feasibility check for this 31st date. We wouldn't move forward with this plan without circling back to talk as a group how much it would or wouldn't save and have a broader discussion.

Thanks for your patience in this red-tape portion of the process. Once we get international flights booked, we'll be able to have some more exciting convos about what sort of fun beach/cultural/adventure excursions we want to do! :flag-ph:

text:
Hey Everyone! We have a great MBA networking event coming up! Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. There will be all sorts of great companies represented there! Including but not limited to McKinsey, Bain, PWC, Slalom, Cicero, Bill, and many more! We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
Free for SCA members and $3 for non-members
Business Casual

text:
Reminder everyone! Slalom Consulting is coming to do an info session on *Wednesday 18th at 6 p.m*. in room TNBR W122. Slalom is an international based consulting firm that does all sorts of consulting. Slalom in Salt Lake focuses on Workforce Transformation. (which to them means any change that a company is working through) Slalom is SLC is open to *full-time students and slalom in the US and globally is looking for interns and full-time.*

 <https://www.slalom.com/>
<https://www.linkedin.com/company/slalom-consulting/>


*Slalom*
*<https://www.slalom.com/|Slalom>*
Slalom is a global consulting firm focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation.


*<http://linkedin.com|linkedin.com>*
*<https://www.linkedin.com/company/slalom-consulting/|Slalom | LinkedIn>*
Slalom | 218,807 followers on LinkedIn. We help people and organizations dream bigger, move faster, and build better tomorrows for all. | Slalom is a purpose-led, global business and technology consulting company. Our purpose—to help people and organizations dream bigger, move faster, and build better tomorrows for all—guides everything we do. And our north star is our vision of a world in which each person has the opportunity to love their life and work.

text:
Hey Everyone! We have a great MBA networking event coming up! Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

Consulting Companies committed: *McKinsey, Bain, PwC, Slalom, Cicero, Clozd* (looking to get more to come)
Strategy Roles/Companies Committed: *Bill, Dees Limited, School Leadership Alliance, Henry Schein One, Security Metrics, BYU TV* (looking to get more to come)

If you are interested in Consulting it will be a great opportunity!

If you are interested in Strategic roles or strategy roles this will be a great opportunity!

Many of these companies are looking for interns and full-time roles or have connections to opportunities!

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
*NOW FREE for everyone - we have decided to drop the fee (thank you, anonymous supporter)*
Business Casual

text:
Hey Everyone! It’s finally here! There will be companies with full-time and internship opportunities at this networking event today Oct 24th at 6pm in the Hinckley Building East Conference room. We are inviting all past MBA SCA Alumni and friends of the program that what to see BYU MBA's get into strategy or consulting roles!

Consulting Companies committed: *McKinsey, Bain, PwC, Slalom, Cicero, Clozd* (looking to get more to come)
Strategy Roles/Companies Committed: *Bill, Dees Limited, School Leadership Alliance, Henry Schein One, Security Metrics, BYU TV* (looking to get more to come)

If you are interested in Consulting it will be a great opportunity!

If you are interested in Strategic roles or strategy roles this will be a great opportunity!

*Many of these companies are looking for interns and full-time roles or have connections to opportunities!*

There will be a soda bar and Hors d'oeuvres
*NOW FREE for everyone - we have decided to drop the fee (thank you, anonymous supporter)*
Business Casual

text:
Hi all, the Think Tank will have its first meeting next Friday, November 3rd at 2:00 p.m. in TNRB 220.
If you have a tech idea put together your "pitch deck" (or a quick PowerPoint to help us visualize the actual idea/product/service), if you have a product then bring an MVP with your pitch deck, or if you're still in the idea phase without a deck or actual product then you can share your idea and we can work with what you have. Also, there are several individuals who don't have their own business ideas but want to be a part of the exciting creation and discovery phases of an early business and they will be a part of the group.

Please reach out if you have any questions before the first meeting next Friday. Also, everyone is invited, this isn't exclusive. Looking forward to seeing you all next week!

The office provides internships, excellent networking with early and growth-stage technology companies, and opportunities to earn significant licensing bounties.

text:
License Bounty Process:
1. Contact Dave Brown at <mailto:dave_brown@byu.edu|dave_brown@byu.edu>
2. Receive and sign NDA
3. Get access to technology list
4. Browse technologies with a few questions in mind
    a. Does this technology interest me?
    b. Do I know anyone in industry who might be interested in licensing this?
    c. Are their companies I am already networking with who would be interested?
5. Reach out to existing contacts and make new ones
6. Refer interested parties to the TTO
7. Remain engaged as much as possible!
8. Make $5k

<!channel> 

Friends, HHHAAAALLLLPPPPP :tired_face: :tired_face: :tired_face: :tired_face: 

I got roped into co-hosting my friend’s 30th birthday and we’re doing a “death to her 20s”, funeralish theme. 

Thanks to Pinterest, I’ve got the food and decor covered, I have absolutely NO idea what to do for entertainment. 

If this were a holiday party, bachelorette, or baby shower, or even the freakin’ White House State Dinner, I’d be dandy. But a BIRTHDAY party at my house for a bunch of women??? I’ve got nothing. :sob:

Does anyone have any tried-and-true games/entertainment ideas for an adult woman’s birthday party?? 

TYIA, you lifesavers! :kissing_heart:

Hi <!channel> of awesome gals and pals- this is event is for YOU! 

Join us this Wednesday from 6-7:15 for the Marriott School Female Faculty Panel!

The purpose of the event is to help you see the female faculty as more of peers and mentors during your time in the MBA.

WIM is helping to sponsor this panel and we would love to have you all there. :heart:  

Register below:
<https://marriott.byu.edu/event/femalepanel2023|https://marriott.byu.edu/event/femalepanel2023>

****We are in need of a few volunteers to help with set-up, run mics, and monitor food. Shoot me a message below if you are willing to help!
